NASA World Cup Entry Form
August, 2003 - Oklahoma City, OK.
Powerlifting, Bench Press Only and Power Sports Championships
Credit Card Instant Entry Form
Date: Saturday, and Sunday, 2003
Location: Biltmore Hotel, 401 S. Meridian Ave., Oklahoma City, OK. 405-947-7681
Meet Director: Rich Peters, P.O. Box 735, Noble, OK. 73068 405-527-8513 sqbpdl@aol.com
Official Weigh-In Times
Early Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 pm, Friday Night (All Women and Men 119-205)
Regular Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 am, Saturday Morning (All Women and Men 119-205)
Early Weigh-In : 8:00-9:00 pm, Saturday Night (Men 227-SHW)
Regular Weigh-In: 8:00-9:00 am, Sunday Morning (Men 227-SHW)
Lifting will begin at 10:00 am both days.

Rules: All Current NASA Rules will apply. View the entire NASA Rule Book on our Web Site at www.nasa-sports.com. All lifters are required to have a current NASA Membership Card. Cards will be available at the meet or can be ordered from our web site. Membership Cards are good for 1 full year from the date of their purchase. Adult Membership is $25.00 per year and Senior Lifters (65+ years old) & High School Memberships are $15.00 per year. All lifters MUST wear a Wrestling Suit or other one piece suit. No Canvas Equipment of any kind Allowed.
Men’s Weight Classes
Women’s Weight Class
Divisions for Powerlifting, Power Sports & Bench Press Only (equipment allowed)
Pure: Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free.
Natural: Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Novice: Life time Anabolic Steroid Free, never one first in any NASA National Meet.
Teenage: 13-19 years of age, Anabolic steroid Free for minimum of 3 years.
High School: Currently HS enrolled lifters, Anabolic Steroid Free for life.
Junior: 13-23 years of age, Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free.
Intermediate: 24-29 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for 3 years minimum.
Sub-Master-1: 30-34 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Sub-Master-2: 35-39 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Sub Master Pure- 30-39 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for lifetime.
Masters-1: 40-49 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-2: 50-59 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-3: 60-69 years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-4: 70+ years of age, Anabolic Steroid Free for minimum 3 years.
Masters-Pure: 40+ years of age, Lifetime Anabolic Steroid Free lifters only.

Rules: All Current NASA Rules will apply. No Supportive Equipment of any kind is allowed in Power Sports Divisions Only. Lifts included in Power Sports are Strict Curl, Bench Press & Deadlift for Total (Full Meet), or you may enter any Individual Lift. Squat is a Single Lift Meet Only in Power Sports. View the entire NASA Rule Book on our Web Site at www.nasa-sports.com. All lifters are required to have a current NASA Membership Card. Cards will be available at the meet or can be ordered from our web site. Membership Cards are good for 1 full year from the date of their purchase. Adult Membership is $25.00 per year and Senior (65+ years old) & High School Memberships are $15.00 per year. All lifters MUST wear a Wrestling Suit or other one piece suit. No Canvas Equipment of any kind allowed.
Power Sports Entry Fee’s Only
“Power Sports Full Meet (Curl, BP & DL) = $50.00
Strict Curl Only= $45.00, Squat Only= $45.00, Bench Only=$45.00, Deadlift Only= $45.00
Combination of Any Two Single Lift Events= $75.00
Any 3 Individual Single Lift Events=$109.95     Any 3 Individual Events & Full Meet = $129.95

Awards: 1st thru 5th Place Awards for each weight class in each Division for Powerlifting, BP Only and Power Sports Contests. Awards will consist of Special Award Clocks, Column Trophies, Large Plaques and Medium Plaques and much more....
Return Entry and Entry Fee’s
Rich Peters, P.O. Box 735, Noble, OK. 73068
Or you may enter on-line from our web site at www.nasa-sports.com
Entry Fee’s

Powerlifting and Bench Press Only (Equipted) : $50.00 for first division entered, $35.00 for each additional entry. Late Fee after Deadline Date is $10.00 additional fee, per division entered. Cash Only for all late entries.
Power Sports Entry Fee’s are posted on the Power Sports portion of this entry form.
Team Entry Fee

$35.00 per Team Entry. This fee is for the Team Trophy. Team Rosters MUST be turned in by the start of lifting on Saturday. Trophies: 1st thru 3rd for Powerlifting, BP Only and Power Sports Teams. Maximum of 10 members per team.
